, and the continuing impact of the texts emphasized. Taken as a whole, the book offers a simple reverence for the achievements of these men and law books and a deep respect for the role historical events have played in the development of the common law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCommon lawxHistory. 0aCommon lawzEnglandxHistory. 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh1 aBoyer, Allen D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyer, Allen D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107042040 cprintz978080475714040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804779593?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804779593423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804779593/original  a978-3-11-070420-4  Stanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles